data.title: Tanaka Farms
data.text:
All Pickers (Ages 3 and up): Mon-Fri $20 | Sat, Sun, & Holidays $24 Children 2 and under are FREE and do not require a ticket, but they do not receive items picked.

Military Servicemembers are FREE! Must show military ID at check-in to receive free admission. Free admission for the servicemember only. Retired, Veteran, or Active Duty. Thank you for your service!

Melon Tasting Tours are back!

Tours depart daily starting July 20! Everyone’s favorite summer tour at Tanaka Farms has finally returned! Nothing beats the summer heat like a big slice of juicy watermelon! Here at Tanaka Farms, we grow lots of different melons! From Canary Melons to Cantaloupe, and Honeydew to the rare Yellow Watermelon!

Take a guided wagon ride around our 30 acre farm to see and learn about how summer fruits and vegetables grow! Make a stop in the fields to harvest a seasonal vegetable, then sit under a shaded tent and sample lots of fresh cut summer squash, different types of melon, and take home a melon of your very own!

Your tour ticket also includes entry to the Corn-O-Copia food festival, Barnyard Educational Exhibit, Pollinator Garden, Free play area for the littles, and lots of photo ops. (Arts & Crafts, food & games are all priced separately.)

$5 per person (Children 2 & under are FREE, Military is FREE) General admission includes entry to the festival grounds, Barnyard Educational Exhibit, Pollinator Garden, Free play area for the littles, and lots of photo ops. Arts & Crafts, food & games are all priced separately.

*We will stop selling activity tickets for Games and Arts & Crafts at 3:30pm.

Corn-O-Copia Celebrates Corn!

Sat & Sun, July 20 & 21 from 10am-4pm! Our Tanaka Farms grown sweet white corn is some of the best corn you’ll ever eat…even raw! So join us for all sorts of foods featuring this summertime staple! Here are just a few of the options that will be available:

Roasted Corn & Toppings Bar (Choose from mayo, butter, chopped cilantro, parmesan cheese, cotija cheese, salt & pepper, hot Cheetos, bacon bits, chili pepper, and cayenne pepper)

Brisket Elote Bowl (BBQ Chopped Brisket, Tanaka Corn, Cream Corn, Chopped Cilantro, Cotija Cheese, Jalapeño slices, Japanese BBQ Sauce)

Roasted Corn & Arugula Salad

Grilled Flatbread with Roasted Tomato Sauce, by itself, or topped with corn & arugula salad

Fusion of Esquites & Korean Corn Cheese in a cup

Roasted Corn Pico with El Nopalito chips

Live entertainment on Saturday, July 20, from 11am to 2pm provided the Celia the Fiddle Girl!

Tanaka Farms is a thirty-acre farm owned and operated by the Tanaka Family right here in the heart of Irvine!

At Tanaka Farms, we believe it is important to connect with where your food comes from. We hope to help you, your friends, and family to do so by offering responsibly farmed produce, farm tours, educational workshops, a barnyard educational center, u-pick activities, luncheons, cookouts, cooking demos, a community-supported agriculture program, and more. Welcome to our farm!

The Tanaka Farms Produce Market Stand is open daily from 9am-5pm
